                        <div id="para15_6" class="para" smil:begin="00:16:13.853" smil:end="00:16:36.853">Now I know that's true because we had information at the time that that provincial committee no longer met in the province. It met over the <span class="tei-name tei-name-Cambodia">Cambodian</span> border someplace. It had lost its contacts with the people. They didn't have their links in to the villages and to the communities they previously had had before the <span class="tei-name tei-name-CORDS">Pacification</span> and the <span class="tei-name tei-name-Phoenix_Program">Phoenix Program</span>.<div class="tei-metadata"><div id="Cambodia">Cambodia
</div><div id="CORDS">Civil Operations and Revolutionary Development Support
</div><div id="Phoenix_Program">Phoenix Program
</div>
</div>
</div>
                        <div id="para15_7" class="para" smil:begin="00:16:36.853" smil:end="00:16:52.970">I reiterate that the <span class="tei-name tei-name-Phoenix_Program">Phoenix Program</span> was only a piece of the larger <span class="tei-name tei-name-CORDS">Pacification Program</span>, and alone it wouldn't have worked. Because the key to the <span class="tei-name tei-name-Phoenix_Program">Phoenix Program</span> was the support of the people against the enemy apparatus.<div class="tei-metadata"><div id="Phoenix_Program">Phoenix Program
